00:13:00.572 --> 00:13:02.532
Oh. that's what I wanted to tell you.

248
00:13:02.533 --> 00:13:03.784
Uh. Ashe is buying in.

249
00:13:06.286 --> 00:13:07.745
Just like that?

250
00:13:07.746 --> 00:13:10.122
Well. subject to due diligence
of the company's financials.

251
00:13:10.123 --> 00:13:12.583
It's standard practice
for all new investments.

252
00:13:12.584 --> 00:13:14.085
Could you just excuse us for a second?

253
00:13:14.086 --> 00:13:15.628
Come on. Nick.

254
00:13:15.629 --> 00:13:16.797
It'll be quick.

255
00:13:25.055 --> 00:13:26.306
What the hell are you doing. Nick?

256
00:13:26.974 --> 00:13:28.683
Oh. look. [stammers]

257
00:13:28.684 --> 00:13:30.893
I-I know.
I know I should have told you sooner.

258
00:13:30.894 --> 00:13:32.311
but it all happened so fast.

259
00:13:32.312 --> 00:13:36.191
I mean. we went out for a drink and boom…
[laughs] …he wants to take us national.

260
00:13:36.775 --> 00:13:40.361
250 Strong Ass Gyms
across the country by 2028.

261
00:13:40.362 --> 00:13:41.779
Yes. I-I heard the spiel.

262
00:13:41.780 --> 00:13:45.408
He was making friends with an NBA star.
but we have a good plan. Nick.

263
00:13:45.409 --> 00:13:46.951
Slow and steady growth.

264
00:13:46.952 --> 00:13:49.288
He'll commit 30 mill.

265
00:13:50.831 --> 00:13:51.914
Thirty million dollars?

266
00:13:51.915 --> 00:13:53.332
[laughs]

267
00:13:53.333 --> 00:13:55.793
He's got a whole franchise team.
We're gonna blow this thing up.

268
00:13:55.794 --> 00:13:57.545
We don't know this guy. Nick.

269
00:13:57.546 --> 00:13:59.589
Well. we've got 30 million
reasons to get to know him.

270
00:13:59.590 --> 00:14:00.673
Not like this.

271
00:14:00.674 --> 00:14:02.842
You take money like that.
and he'll own you.

272
00:14:02.843 --> 00:14:05.678
- Okay. Calm down.
- There is a process to this. okay?

273
00:14:05.679 --> 00:14:07.430
And why is he looking through our books?

274
00:14:07.431 --> 00:14:09.765
- Don't you mean my books?
- I want to look at his books.

275
00:14:09.766 --> 00:14:12.268
I want to talk to his bankers.
I want to check his credit.

276
00:14:12.269 --> 00:14:13.561
I can't let you do this. Nick--

277
00:14:13.562 --> 00:14:14.980
Hey!

278
00:14:16.773 --> 00:14:18.192
I don't work for you.

279
00:14:19.026 --> 00:14:20.443
Okay. Okay. That's not what I meant.

280
00:14:20.444 --> 00:14:21.652
Matter of fact. you work for me.

281
00:14:21.653 --> 00:14:22.820
- I know.
- Do you?

282
00:14:22.821 --> 00:14:27.659
Yes. yes. and it's my job
to protect you from deals like this.

283
00:14:32.206 --> 00:14:33.207
[scoffs]

284
00:14:36.835 --> 00:14:39.838
Look. man. I was an NBA champion.

285
00:14:40.672 --> 00:14:44.634
I don't go from that to running a gym.
or-or two gyms.

286
00:14:44.635 --> 00:14:46.594
I need to leave a bigger mark than that.

287
00:14:46.595 --> 00:14:48.888
You're blowing up all over TV. Nick.

288
00:14:48.889 --> 00:14:50.181
[scoffs] Maybe.

289
00:14:50.182 --> 00:14:54.519
Or maybe the NBA makes a new network deal
and I'm out on my ass in two years.

290
00:14:54.520 --> 00:14:56.312
You said it yourself. Barney.

291
00:14:56.313 --> 00:14:58.105
Former athletes have a window.

292
00:14:58.106 --> 00:15:02.069
and I know mine will close
before I'm ready. just like my career did.

293
00:15:02.861 --> 00:15:04.111
If I've learned anything.

294
00:15:04.112 --> 00:15:09.034
it's that when an opportunity
like this comes around. I have to grab it.

295
00:15:13.080 --> 00:15:17.459
You can get on board. or you can quit.
but I'm doing this.

296
00:15:19.294 --> 00:15:20.921
Gentlemen. is there a problem?

297
00:15:23.215 --> 00:15:24.967
Is there a problem. Barney?

298
00:15:26.552 --> 00:15:28.469
Mr. DeMille. was it?

299
00:15:28.470 --> 00:15:29.513
[DeMille] That's right.

300
00:15:31.849 --> 00:15:33.058
How can I help?

301
00:15:35.269 --> 00:15:38.271
[DeMille] Well. for starters.
I'm gonna need all your passwords.

302
00:15:38.272 --> 00:15:39.565
Of course you will.

303
00:16:08.051 --> 00:16:12.054
[Coop] The Fairy Melusine<i>.
built in 2012 by Nereids Yachts.</i>

304
00:16:12.055 --> 00:16:14.724
<i>the apex of nautical luxury.</i>

305
00:16:14.725 --> 00:16:16.934
<i>If you have fuck-you money.
you buy a modest.</i>

306
00:16:16.935 --> 00:16:19.478
<i>entry-level Nereids
for around three million.</i>

307
00:16:19.479 --> 00:16:22.481
<i>If you have fuck-it-all money.
you have them design a mega yacht</i>

308
00:16:22.482 --> 00:16:26.485
<i>to your custom specifications.
for a price on par with a naval destroyer.</i>

309
00:16:26.486 --> 00:16:28.154
<i>And you give them one directive…</i>

310
00:16:28.155 --> 00:16:29.572
<i>length over all.</i>

311
00:16:29.573 --> 00:16:32.950
<i>At 197 feet with a 875 gross tonnage.</i>

312
00:16:32.951 --> 00:16:35.620
The Fairy Melusine <i>is powered
by Caterpillar engines</i>

313
00:16:35.621 --> 00:16:39.208
<i>that give her 5.000 horsepower
and a maximum speed of 17 knots.</i>

314
00:16:40.501 --> 00:16:42.126
{\an8}<i>Nothing lets the millionaires know</i>

315
00:16:42.127 --> 00:16:45.422
{\an8}<i>you're a billionaire
like owning a custom white boat.</i>

316
00:16:46.131 --> 00:16:47.632
Oh. Jesus.

317
00:16:47.633 --> 00:16:49.259
[phone ringing]

318
00:16:50.344 --> 00:16:52.386
I gotta take this.
Uh. go ahead. I'll catch up.

319
00:16:52.387 --> 00:16:54.139
I'll just be a second. Yeah. Barney?

320
00:16:55.432 --> 00:16:58.267
- So. some news.
- [Coop] <i>Yeah. now's not a great time.</i>

321
00:16:58.268 --> 00:17:00.312
Ashe is investing in the gym.

322
00:17:01.230 --> 00:17:04.232
What? You mean…
[stutters] …he's considering it?

323
00:17:04.233 --> 00:17:06.692
<i>No. no.
He seems to have already committed.</i>

324
00:17:06.693 --> 00:17:08.193
And Nick didn't tell you?

325
00:17:08.194 --> 00:17:09.655
<i>No. he did. Today.</i>

326
00:17:10.656 --> 00:17:12.240
Well. can you talk him out of it?

327
00:17:12.241 --> 00:17:13.574
<i>I was hoping you would.</i>

328
00:17:13.575 --> 00:17:15.826
It would be highly
suspicious for his business manager

329
00:17:15.827 --> 00:17:17.579
to try to talk him
out of 30 million bucks.

330
00:17:19.748 --> 00:17:20.831
Thirty million?

331
00:17:20.832 --> 00:17:23.042
<i>Yeah.
they're looking at the books as we speak.</i>

332
00:17:23.627 --> 00:17:26.712
- Well. that's not good. Are you worried?
- No.

333
00:17:26.713 --> 00:17:27.714
<i>You sound worried.</i>

334
00:17:28.257 --> 00:17:31.092
Well. I'm worried I might get worried.

335
00:17:31.093 --> 00:17:33.135
Look. I'm sure Ashe
is just putting on a show

336
00:17:33.136 --> 00:17:35.137
to let Nick know
how serious he is about this.

337
00:17:35.138 --> 00:17:37.139
It's a… It's a perfunctory review.

338
00:17:37.140 --> 00:17:39.976
They won't get into cash flow.
It'll be fine. we're fine. I'm fine.

339
00:17:39.977 --> 00:17:41.186
I got this.

340
00:17:43.522 --> 00:17:45.064
I got this. [sighs]

341
00:17:45.065 --> 00:17:46.316
[line beeps]

342
00:17:53.782 --> 00:17:55.283
Ms. Birch is finishing her call.

343
00:17:55.284 --> 00:17:56.368
Ah. thank you.

344
00:17:57.619 --> 00:17:58.829
- Here we are.
- Good.

345
00:18:07.713 --> 00:18:09.130
[speaking Serbian]

346
00:18:09.131 --> 00:18:11.465
[Coop] <i>Cricket Birch made her money
the old-fashioned way.</i>

347
00:18:11.466 --> 00:18:12.550
<i>She inherited it.</i>

348
00:18:12.551 --> 00:18:14.844
<i>But that didn't make her
any less formidable.</i>

349
00:18:14.845 --> 00:18:16.804
[Coop]
<i>She was Oxford educated. boardroom tested.</i>

350
00:18:16.805 --> 00:18:18.014
<i>and unlike many of her ilk.</i>

351
00:18:18.015 --> 00:18:20.683
<i>she had actually grown
the principal instead of squandering it.</i>

352
00:18:20.684 --> 00:18:23.311
<i>Which made her something of
a unicorn in the financial world.</i>

353
00:18:23.312 --> 00:18:24.687
<i>And. if the rumors were true.</i>

354
00:18:24.688 --> 00:18:27.148
<i>on certain
highly-exclusive dating apps as well.</i>

355
00:18:27.149 --> 00:18:29.568
[speaking Serbian]

356
00:18:34.698 --> 00:18:39.702
- Jack. lovely to see you as always.
- You too. Cricket.

357
00:18:39.703 --> 00:18:42.246
Oh. Uh. you remember Andrew Cooper?

358
00:18:42.247 --> 00:18:44.665
Hello. Coop. It's been a minute.

359
00:18:44.666 --> 00:18:45.875
[Coop] That it has. Nice boat.

360
00:18:45.876 --> 00:18:47.920
[laughs] This old thing.

361
00:18:48.754 --> 00:18:49.755
Shall we?

362
00:18:54.426 --> 00:18:57.136
You'll see Coop's investment
shifts a sizable portion

363
00:18:57.137 --> 00:18:59.680
of the fund's beta to equity.
mitigating your exposure.

364
00:18:59.681 --> 00:19:01.098
- It's okay. Jack.
- And by Q4. you could--

365
00:19:01.099 --> 00:19:03.560
I don't need the dogs and ponies.
I've done the math.

366
00:19:04.853 --> 00:19:06.563
I'll have to come ready. right?

367
00:19:07.814 --> 00:19:11.485
All right. so tell me. what can we do
to make you more comfortable with this?

368
00:19:12.486 --> 00:19:14.530
You can't. I mean. not really.

369
00:19:15.364 --> 00:19:17.616
I'll either be comfortable. or I won't be.

370
00:19:18.242 --> 00:19:19.617
Why are we here?

371
00:19:19.618 --> 00:19:22.621
Because you're an old-school closer.
and I love that about you.

372
00:19:23.455 --> 00:19:24.665
[scoffs]

373
00:19:26.166 --> 00:19:27.167
[Jack sighs]

374
00:19:28.544 --> 00:19:33.006
I've had some Strottarga Bianco
escorted from Austria for you.

375
00:19:33.882 --> 00:19:35.758
That's very kind of you.

376
00:19:35.759 --> 00:19:37.635
I will definitely try some
before we leave.

377
00:19:37.636 --> 00:19:40.430
Oh. no. You should try it now
while it's still fresh.

378
00:19:46.770 --> 00:19:48.688
Uh. how can I say no to that?

379
00:19:48.689 --> 00:19:50.107
[groans]

380
00:19:59.449 --> 00:20:01.076
Well. you've been awfully quiet.

381
00:20:02.369 --> 00:20:05.246
Yeah. well. Jack had a plan.

382
00:20:05.247 --> 00:20:08.875
Yeah. to bore me
into submission. I'm sure.

383
00:20:08.876 --> 00:20:11.086
Now the adults can speak freely.

384
00:20:13.589 --> 00:20:14.756
You first.

385
00:20:16.133 --> 00:20:19.802
Okay. Well.
I'm managing a sizable chunk right now.

386
00:20:19.803 --> 00:20:23.806
If Jack did to me what he did to you.
I would be out for revenge.

387
00:20:23.807 --> 00:20:27.268
Not handing his company a management fee
on a nine-figure investment.

388
00:20:27.269 --> 00:20:29.688
so you're gonna forgive me
if I'm feeling a little suspicious.

389
00:20:30.772 --> 00:20:32.148
Okay.

390
00:20:32.149 --> 00:20:35.318
Well. if it makes you feel any better.
I've already gotten my revenge.

391
00:20:35.319 --> 00:20:36.612
You mean the Swiss.

392
00:20:37.279 --> 00:20:40.115
Oh. don't look so impressed.
There's very few secrets in our world.

393
00:20:45.037 --> 00:20:47.915
Look. Jack's the devil I know. that's all.

394
00:20:48.498 --> 00:20:51.793
Yeah. that may be true.
but it's definitely not all.

395
00:20:53.712 --> 00:20:55.546
Losing the Swiss hurt him.

396
00:20:55.547 --> 00:20:58.132
Bailey had to take the hit.
and it was a big hit.

397
00:20:58.133 --> 00:21:03.555
but somehow Jack managed
to preserve Excelsior's returns.

398
00:21:04.223 --> 00:21:05.765
You don't need to look so impressed.

399
00:21:05.766 --> 00:21:07.559
You're not the only one
that does the math.

400
00:21:08.727 --> 00:21:11.187
So. I don't know
what your arrangement is with Jack.

401
00:21:11.188 --> 00:21:13.315
and I honestly don't really care.

402
00:21:13.941 --> 00:21:16.859
I just know that Excelsior
is as close to bulletproof as it gets.

403
00:21:16.860 --> 00:21:19.196
and that's where I want to be.

404
00:21:20.614 --> 00:21:21.907
And it's as simple as that?

405
00:21:22.741 --> 00:21:25.869
Well. no. but… That's the gist of it.

406
00:21:28.539 --> 00:21:31.165
- I don't want any hot money. Coop.
- This isn't that.

407
00:21:31.166 --> 00:21:33.501
No redemptions six months in
because your investors

408
00:21:33.502 --> 00:21:34.919
don't have the balls for a down market.

409
00:21:34.920 --> 00:21:38.214
- I'm playing the long game.
- And I'm not looking for a partner.

410
00:21:38.215 --> 00:21:39.883
- I call the shots.
- Understood.

411
00:21:40.425 --> 00:21:42.427
I just want to ride your coattails.

412
00:21:48.725 --> 00:21:51.186
I'm having a party tonight. Can you stay?

413
00:21:52.396 --> 00:21:57.900
Hi. Uh. I need some Humboldt Fog.
double the Manchego. Smokin' Goat…

414
00:21:57.901 --> 00:21:59.944
- You know what. he's gonna want a Brie.
- Right.

415
00:21:59.945 --> 00:22:02.071
Uh. which one's
the one with the moon in the title?

416
00:22:02.072 --> 00:22:03.155
Oh. um…

417
00:22:03.156 --> 00:22:04.700
- [phone buzzing]
- Oh. excuse me.

418
00:22:05.742 --> 00:22:06.743
One minute.

419
00:22:08.996 --> 00:22:10.705
- Hello?
- [Chivo] <i>Elena?</i>

420
00:22:10.706 --> 00:22:12.748
[in Spanish] Oh. Chivo.
What number is this?

421
00:22:12.749 --> 00:22:15.042
<i>Elena… I need a favor.</i>

422
00:22:15.043 --> 00:22:18.213
Can it wait? I'm underwater
with Nick's housewarming.

423
00:22:19.006 --> 00:22:20.382
I got arrested.

424
00:22:21.592 --> 00:22:22.593
What?

425
00:22:23.510 --> 00:22:25.887
<i>I was with Luis. and--</i>

426
00:22:25.888 --> 00:22:27.388
Wait. Félix's Luis?

427
00:22:27.389 --> 00:22:29.390
Are you kidding me?

428
00:22:29.391 --> 00:22:32.227
Elena! I need you to get me
the fuck out of here.

429
00:22:33.395 --> 00:22:36.231
Okay. I'll be there as soon as I can.

430
00:22:37.566 --> 00:22:39.610
Bail is fifty thousand bucks.

431
00:22:41.236 --> 00:22:43.613
Fifty thousand!

432
00:22:43.614 --> 00:22:45.907
What the fuck did you do?

433
00:22:45.908 --> 00:22:47.450
No. I can't.

434
00:22:47.451 --> 00:22:49.995
Elena?

435
00:22:51.288 --> 00:22:54.332
[line ringing]

436
00:22:54.333 --> 00:22:56.919
- [in English] <i>Hey. This is Andrew Cooper.</i>
- [sighs]

437
00:23:05.385 --> 00:23:08.263
So. how long have you
been working for Mr. Ashe?

438
00:23:10.140 --> 00:23:11.558
Long time.

439
00:23:12.226 --> 00:23:13.977
- Well…
- [phone ringing]

440
00:23:14.645 --> 00:23:15.979
[sniffs. clears throat]

441
00:23:16.647 --> 00:23:19.024
Uh. this is a client. excuse me.

442
00:23:20.192 --> 00:23:21.193
[Elena] <i>Barney.</i>

443
00:23:21.944 --> 00:23:23.444
Can I call you back?

444
00:23:23.445 --> 00:23:24.821
<i>I need my money.</i>

445
00:23:25.364 --> 00:23:27.031
Okay. this doesn't work like an ATM.

446
00:23:27.032 --> 00:23:29.575
This is an emergency. okay?
I don't care how it works.

447
00:23:29.576 --> 00:23:31.370
I-I need $50.000 today.

448
00:23:32.955 --> 00:23:35.998
That's a bit complicated at the moment.

449
00:23:35.999 --> 00:23:37.083
<i>Complicated how?</i>

450
00:23:37.084 --> 00:23:39.585
You have all my money.
I need some of it back.

451
00:23:39.586 --> 00:23:40.920
You didn't hold on to any of it?

452
00:23:40.921 --> 00:23:42.631
<i>You told me I didn't need to.</i>

453
00:23:43.257 --> 00:23:44.674
- [sighs. stutters]
- [employee] Mr. DeMille.

454
00:23:44.675 --> 00:23:46.301
would you come take a look at this?

455
00:23:47.761 --> 00:23:50.179
- Uh. I'm gonna have to call you back.
- <i>Barney. do not hang up on me.</i>

456
00:23:50.180 --> 00:23:51.431
Okay. then.

457
00:23:53.100 --> 00:23:55.018
[sighs]

458
00:23:58.856 --> 00:24:00.774
["Katazitite" playing]

459
00:24:11.368 --> 00:24:14.371
[partygoers chattering. cheering]

460
00:24:39.730 --> 00:24:41.148
[phone chimes]

461
00:24:44.484 --> 00:24:46.111
[exhales deeply]

462
00:24:53.744 --> 00:24:55.870
I don't recall
you being such an introvert.

463
00:24:55.871 --> 00:24:57.247
[Coop laughs]

464
00:24:58.665 --> 00:25:00.334
Not really my crowd.

465
00:25:00.959 --> 00:25:02.586
No. I didn't think so.

466
00:25:05.547 --> 00:25:08.217
You're very different since
the last time we saw each other.

467
00:25:09.259 --> 00:25:10.260
Older.

468
00:25:11.094 --> 00:25:12.221
Sadder.

469
00:25:13.514 --> 00:25:15.015
Well… [sighs]

470
00:25:15.516 --> 00:25:17.391
A lot has happened
since the last time I saw you.

471
00:25:17.392 --> 00:25:19.018
Yeah. I heard about it.

472
00:25:19.019 --> 00:25:20.854
Oh. Well. then. you know.

473
00:25:22.606 --> 00:25:25.066
- Hope you don't hold it against me.
- What? With my family?

474
00:25:25.067 --> 00:25:26.693
[scoffs] It's nothing.

475
00:25:29.530 --> 00:25:32.074
- And you got divorced.
- I did.

476
00:25:32.866 --> 00:25:34.117
Was it bad?

477
00:25:35.744 --> 00:25:36.745
[sighs]

478
00:25:37.538 --> 00:25:38.622
Still is.

479
00:25:40.249 --> 00:25:41.708
I'm really sorry. Coop.

480
00:25:42.835 --> 00:25:47.005
You were one of the rare faithful ones.
or at least where I was concerned.

481
00:25:48.131 --> 00:25:50.049
It was impressive.

482
00:25:50.050 --> 00:25:53.553
Ah. yes. well.
it turns out there's a whole hell

483
00:25:53.554 --> 00:25:56.348
of a lot more to being married
than just not cheating.

484
00:25:57.641 --> 00:25:58.684
Who knew?

485
00:25:59.726 --> 00:26:01.811
Do you remember the conference in Berlin?

486
00:26:01.812 --> 00:26:03.563
- [laughs]
- [chuckles]

487
00:26:03.564 --> 00:26:05.231
I remember we were both pretty drunk.

